  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    StringTree<Val>  
    Tree<T>
    provides a tree-structure for collecting and storing data Notes: this class CAN be threadsafe, if specified.
    Tree.InternalIDHelper
    applys a ID, which is unique inside of this tree, to every node inside the tree the InternalIDHelper for a tree is always held by the treeroot if a subtree is newly added to a tree, all IDs have to be changed by the InternalIDHelper of the tree which holds the subtree if a subtree is removed from a tree, a new InternalIDHelper will be applied to this Tree and all IDs will be updated
    Tree.TreeGlobalVarHelper
    controlls all objects that are used globally in this tree
    Tree.TreeOpHelper<R>  
    Tree.TreeScheduler
    if this tree is threadsafe, this scheduler will controll reading and writing access to avoid data inconsitency and handle the priority of these tasks only one access at once, aswell reading as writing
    Tree.TreeTask<R>
    represents a task in this tree
    TreeMap<Key,Val>
    creates a treemap that can be used to relate every key to a value.
